# Workflow Hub Frontend — project rules

## Rule 0 — follow `ai-rules/` (MANDATORY)

Coding standards live in sibling repo `../ai-rules/` (absolute:
`C:\Users\rishi.alluri\OneDrive - McKissock LP\Documents\Projects\ai-rules`).

1. Start at `../ai-rules/RULES-INDEX.md`, then `frontend/00-index/frontend-rules-index.md`.
2. Load **only** 2–5 task-matching frontend rule files per change.
3. Always include: `folder-structure-and-boundary-rules.md`, `naming-and-file-rules.md`,
   `forbidden-patterns-rules.md` (under `frontend/01-architecture/` and `frontend/05-quality/`).
4. See `.cursor/rules/ai-rules.mdc` for the full loading protocol.

## Rule 1 — design-reference for ALL UI/design decisions (MANDATORY)

Before building or changing any UI, read the sibling design-reference repo:

- Relative: `../workflowHub-design-reference/`
- Absolute: `C:\Users\rishi.alluri\OneDrive - McKissock LP\Documents\Projects\workflowHub-design-reference`

Consult `colors_and_type.css` (tokens), `app.css` (styles), `app.jsx` (shell), `ui.jsx`
(primitives), and the relevant `screens*.jsx` for the screen. Match layout and visual intent;
implement in Angular + Tailwind + PrimeNG. **Never** import or ship reference code.
See `.cursor/rules/design-reference.mdc` when editing `frontend/**` UI files.

## Related repos

- **Backend API:** `../workflowHub-backend/`
- **Product spec:** `workflowHub-prd-v2.md` in this repo

## Tech stack

- **Angular 20** (standalone, application builder), Tailwind CSS, PrimeNG, SCSS
- **API:** `environment.apiBaseUrl` — `/api` with proxy in local dev

## Repository layout

```
frontend/src/app/  → core/ (singletons), shared/ (reusable UI), features/ (auth, workflows, home)
```

## Conventions

- **Rules first** — load relevant `../ai-rules/` frontend files before writing code.
- **Design first** — check `../workflowHub-design-reference/` before any UI/layout/styling work.
- **Match the PRD** for feature behavior; coordinate API changes with `workflowHub-backend`.
- **Angular prefix is `wh`** (e.g. `wh-root`).
- **No secrets in source control** (Google client ID is public; no JWT keys here).

## Commands

- Frontend (`frontend/`): `npm install`, `npm start -- --port 4290`, `npm run build`, `npm test`
- Dev URL: http://localhost:4290/
